interview:q062 a interview:Question ;
    schema:name "Design a distributed task scheduler" ;
    interview:domain interview:systemDesign ;
    interview:difficulty "hard" ;
    interview:tags "system-design, distributed-systems, scheduling, reliability, queues" ;
    interview:timeEstimate "35-45 minutes" ;
    interview:accommodation interview:accommodation002, interview:accommodation003 ;
    interview:suggestedAnswer interview:a062 .

interview:a062 a interview:Answer ;
    interview:keyPoints "Requirements: schedule tasks, execute at specific time, retry failures, horizontal scaling; Components: task queue (Redis/RabbitMQ), scheduler service, worker pool, task registry, monitoring; Patterns: delayed queues, cron expressions, priority queues; Distributed: leader election for scheduler (Raft/ZooKeeper), worker pool for execution, task sharding; Reliability: at-least-once delivery, idempotency, retry with backoff; Consider: task dependencies, recurring tasks, SLA monitoring" ;
    interview:example "Schedule task -> store in DB with execution time -> scheduler polls for due tasks -> publish to queue -> workers consume -> execute -> update status -> retry on failure; Distributed: partition tasks by hash, leader coordinates; Recurring: cron parser determines next run; Priority: separate queues per priority" ;
    interview:pitfalls "Single scheduler (SPOF); no idempotency; missing retry logic; not handling time zones; ignoring task dependencies; no monitoring" .

